## Java (java)

Java project using spring (maven wrapper).

### Conventions
- Follow standard Java naming conventions (PascalCase for classes, camelCase for methods).
- Run the tests with ./mvnw -B verify before finishing a task.
- Do not add new dependencies without declaring them in the existing build tool.

### Architecture
- Respect the layered separation (controller/service/repository) if the project already uses it.
- Prefer dependency injection over manual instantiation when the framework already provides it.

## Canonical commands

- test: \`./mvnw -B verify\` (ci: build.yml)
- build: \`./gradlew build\` (ci: build.yml)

## Structure

- \`.github/\` — GitHub workflows and configuration
- \`src/\` — source code
- \`src/test/\` — tests
- \`src/test/java/\` — tests

## What CI runs (GitHub Actions)

- \`./mvnw -B verify\` (build.yml)
- \`./gradlew build\` (build.yml)",
