## JavaScript (js-ts)

JavaScript project using express.

### Conventions
- Run the tests with npm test before finishing a task.
- Follow the existing CommonJS style (require()/module.exports); do not mix in import/export.

### Architecture
- Keep components/modules small and single-purpose.
- Place tests next to the code they cover or in a mirrored \`test/\` directory, following what the repo already uses.

## Canonical commands

- test: \`npm test\` (package.json)
- lint: \`npm run lint\` (package.json)

## Repo commands

- \`npm test\` → \`mocha --recursive test/\` (package.json)
- \`npm run lint\` → \`eslint lib/ test/\` (package.json)

## Structure

- \`.github/\` — GitHub workflows and configuration
- \`lib/\` — source code
- \`test/\` — tests
- \`test/acceptance/\` — tests
- entry point: \`lib/app.js\` (package.json "main")

## What CI runs (GitHub Actions)

- \`npm ci\` (ci.yml)
- \`npm test\` (ci.yml)
- \`npm run lint\` (ci.yml)",
}
`;

